obo:ECO_0006054  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2978  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.7: \"Sept7 Localization and Mobility Is Regulated by TAOK2 Mediated Phosphorylation\"\n- \"We next tested whether phosphorylation of Sept7 at T426 changed its dynamics of assembly. By measuring the fluorescence recovery after photobleaching, we found that GFP-tagged Sept7 T426D enriched at the spines was more stable than the phosphomutant Sept7 T426A that accumulated at the base of the dendritic spine.\"\n- \"In neurons transfected with phosphomimetic or wild-type Sept7 along with the synaptic scaffolding protein PSD95, we observed much greater co-localization of Sept7T426D with PSD95 in the spine head as compared to Sept7WT (Figures 7G and 7H). \"\n\nFig.8: \"Phosphorylated Sept7 Interacts with PSD95 and Restricts Its Mobility\"\n- \"Using the pSept7 (T426) antibody, we found that phosphorylated Sept7 co-immunoprecipitated with PSD95 from mouse brain lysates, indicating that phosphorylated Sept7 and PSD95 interact in vivo (Figure S7E)\"\n- \"Moreover, endogenous PSD95 from the brain lysate was pulled down by Sept7-CWT that was incubated with wild-type TAOK2, but not the kinase-dead mutant, whereas mutation of T426 to alanine completely abolished the interaction between Sept7 C-terminal tail and PSD95(Figures 8A,S7F, and S7G).\". Experimental description: - \"Neuronal Cultures and Transfection: Hippocampi were obtained from E18 Sprague-Dawley rat (Harlan Lab) embryos...\"\n- \"Human TAOK2 cDNA in pCMV sport 6.0 (Ultanir et al., 2014) ...\"\n- \"Rat and human Septin7 cDNA clones were purchased from ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-04-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2978" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

